ATTENTION RHS STUDENTS: YEARBOOKS HAVE ARRIVED!

You may pick up your yearbook at RHS on Tuesday, July 28th from 11:00 a.m. - 1:00 p.m.

Please adhere to the following guidelines:

1. Drive through the circle in front of RHS and remain in your vehicle.
2. No one will be allowed out of their vehicle and you will not be within six feet of anyone during this pick up.
3. Someone will come to your vehicle and ask for the name and then deliver your yearbook.
4. All staff handing out material will have on a face covering and gloves for your protection and we ask that you have a face covering on as well.

RMSD BUDGET SURVEY 2020-21
The District is in the process of preparing the budget for the upcoming 2020-2021 school year. Please take a few minutes to complete the budget survey questions located at:
https://www.surveymonkey.com/r/rmsdbudgetsurvey2021

The survey will close at 6:00am on April 30, 2020. We will also post the survey on the District’s social media outlets in order to solicit input from parents and the community.

Additionally, Board of Education Budget Study Session information can be found at the following url:
https://www.ruidososchools.org/Budgets.aspx

post_text: Zach Flowers is an 8th-grade student at RMS. He is a member of the yearbook staff and a member of the RMS Choir. He is the voice of the morning announcements at RMS. He likes to sing Karaoke at the Elks Lodge with his father. Zach has a sister that attends WME and his parents teach at Mescalero Apache Schools. He says that he and his family like to watch movies together. He enjoys technology in his spare time, mostly gaming and animating. He hopes to become a software engineer when he gets older. Zach has his own Youtube channel that highlights his favorite cartoon character, Peter Griffin, from Family Guy.

post_text: White Mountain Elementary School’s Student of the Month is Sierra Ahidley. Sierra is in Ms. Brownrigg’s 4th-grade classroom. Sierra is a bright, caring, and respectful student. She works well in a team or on her own. She enjoys learning about science as she likes to find answers to her questions. She is a member of the Turquoise Club at school and likes to sell items to raise funds for going to the Gathering of Nations Pow Wow in Albuquerque when she is in the 5th grade. Sierra likes going to Pow Wows in order to learn more about her culture. In her free time, Sierra likes to sing and draw. She is taking piano lessons and has set a goal to learn to play Decided to Follow Jesus. She loves to ride her bike with her Aunt Candace when they have time. WME is proud to recognize students such as Sierra.

post_text:
Ruidoso Middle School - November Student of the Month. Congratulations to Cade Holland!

He is a 6th-grade student at RMS! Cade’s favorite subject in school is Language Arts. He plays flag football for the Raiders and his favorite board game is chess. Cade has an older brother and he has one dog. His favorite ice cream flavor is cookie dough. Cade likes to read in his spare time. His favorite book is Lord of the Rings. He wants to go to the University of Texas. He wants to go to college to become a teacher. He wants to be a teacher in reading or mathematics.

post_text: Warrior Football received a first-round playoff berth and will host St. Pius this Friday night at Horton Stadium. Kickoff is scheduled for 7:00pm. This marks the 10th consecutive year that Warrior Football has made the state playoffs. Only Ruidoso and Silver in the 4A football playoff bracket can claim this distinction. Congratulations Coach Johnson and Warrior Football past and present! Hope to see everyone there on Friday. Go Warriors!

post_text: High 5 Award Ceremony Follow Up! We had great attendance from our students, families, and faculty to honor those students who scored exceptionally high on the New Mexico Transition Assessment. Our Teepee Lounge supported by our Ruidoso High School culinary students served delicious hors d’ oeuvres. The award ceremony was conducted by Superintendent, Dr. Bickert and RMSD Board President, Luther Light. Thank you to all who came out to honor and congratulate these students on their achievement.
